namespace ScholarPath.Infrastructure.Persistence.Seed;

/// <summary>
/// Realistic English + Arabic bodies for the curated <c>KnowledgeDocument</c>
/// (FAQ) rows seeded into the RAG knowledge base. Each pair is hand-written,
/// 300+ words, and uses the same prose voice as the public FAQ. The RAG
/// retriever injects this content as grounding context for the chatbot, so
/// the wording should read like an authoritative answer rather than a
/// marketing blurb.
/// </summary>
internal static class KnowledgeBodies
{
    public const string PlatformFaqEn =
        "ScholarPath is a bilingual scholarship discovery and application platform for students from the Middle East and North Africa who want to study abroad. The platform brings together four kinds of users — students, scholarship-provider companies, independent consultants and platform admins — so the entire scholarship journey, from discovering an opportunity to landing the offer, happens in one place. " +
        "Students sign up for free, complete a short onboarding that captures their academic background, financial situation and target countries, then receive personalised scholarship recommendations. They can save scholarships, track applications across statuses (Researching, In Progress, Submitted, Accepted, Rejected, Waitlisted), upload supporting documents, book paid consultations with verified consultants, and message providers and consultants directly. " +
        "Companies publish and manage scholarship listings, review applications submitted in-app, and access analytics on applicant pipelines. Consultants set their availability, host paid sessions through the integrated meeting room, and publish learning resources to the Resources Hub. Admins moderate the community forum, approve resources before publication, oversee payments and payouts, and manage platform settings. " +
        "All payments inside the platform — consultations and company reviews — flow through Stripe with profit-sharing configured per transaction type. The Resources Hub holds the platform's editorial content: guides, articles, checklists and videos in English and Arabic. The Community forum hosts threaded discussions across more than eight categories. A retrieval-augmented AI assistant answers questions using both the live scholarship catalogue and a curated FAQ knowledge base — the same one this document belongs to. " +
        "If you ever get stuck, the support email is published in the platform settings and the help center links from every page footer.";

