        "بعد الموافقة. تُعاد جوازات السفر الممهورة عادةً عبر شركة شحن خلال أسبوع إلى أسبوعين. يمكن لطلاب F-1 دخول الولايات المتحدة قبل 30 يوماً كحد أقصى من تاريخ بداية البرنامج المذكور في I-20.";

    public const string VisaSchengenEn =
        "Schengen student visas cover study in any of the 27 member states; rules are broadly aligned but issued by each country's consulate, so the document set varies by destination. The general framework: a long-stay D-type visa for programmes over 90 days, converted on arrival into a residence permit. " +
        "Common requirements. An acceptance letter from a recognised institution, proof of accommodation, financial evidence (varies by country — Germany requires a blocked account of about €11,904 for 12 months at the time of writing; France requires €615 per month evidenced through scholarship letters or sponsorship; Spain accepts a parent's bank statement), valid health insurance, and a clean criminal record. " +
        "Where to apply. Always at the consulate of your destination country. If you live in a country where the destination does not have a consulate, the rules are specific and worth checking — some countries route Schengen applications through a designated VFS or TLS centre. " +
        "Timing. Most countries open the appointment slot three months before the programme start date. Slot availability for popular destinations like Germany and France can fill within days; apply for the appointment as soon as you accept the offer, even if your documents are not all ready. " +
        "After arrival. A Schengen D-visa is typically valid for 90 days from the date of entry. Within that window you must register with the local town hall or immigration office to obtain your residence permit. The deadline varies by country — Germany within 14 days of arrival, France within 90 days, Italy within 8 working days. Missing the deadline can void your stay rights.";

